Advanced Lane Finding Project¶

The goals / steps of this project are the following:

  • Compute the camera calibration matrix and distortion coefficients given a set of chessboard images.
  • Apply a distortion correction to raw images.
  • Use color transforms, gradients, etc., to create a thresholded binary image.
  • Apply a perspective transform to rectify binary image ("birds-eye view").
  • Detect lane pixels and fit to find the lane boundary.
  • Determine the curvature of the lane and vehicle position with respect to center.
  • Warp the detected lane boundaries back onto the original image.
  • Output visual display of the lane boundaries and numerical estimation of lane curvature and vehicle position.

First, I'll compute the camera calibration using chessboard images¶

#Find chessboard corners
for fname in images_cal:
    img = cv2.imread(fname)
    gray = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

    # Find the chessboard corners
    ret, corners = cv2.findChessboardCorners(gray, (9,6),None)

    # If found, add object points, image points
    if ret == True:
        objpoints.append(objp)
        imgpoints.append(corners)

ret, cameramatrix, dist, rvecs, tvecs=cv2.calibrateCamera(objpoints, imgpoints, img_size[:2],None,None)

    image=cv2.undistort(image,matrix,dist,None,matrix)

#Combining thresholds below and CLAHE
def hls_thres(image):
    image=undistort(image,cameramatrix,dist)
    #image=cv2.bilateralFilter(image,15,75,75)
    height=image.shape[0]
    width=image.shape[1]      
#   hls=cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_RGB2HLS)
#   luv=cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_RGB2LUV)
    
    lab=cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_BGR2Lab)
    l=lab[:,:,0]
    a=lab[:,:,1]
    b=lab[:,:,2]
    
    #Calibration 
    a_min_thresh=120
    a_max_thresh=255
    b_min_thresh=150
    b_max_thresh=255
    l_min_thresh=190
    l_max_thresh=255
    
    binary_a=np.zeros_like(a)
    binary_b=np.zeros_like(b)
    binary_l=np.zeros_like(l)
    
    binary_a[(a>a_min_thresh)&(a<=a_max_thresh)]=1
    binary_b[(b>b_min_thresh)&(b<=b_max_thresh)]=1
    binary_l[(l>l_min_thresh)&(l<=l_max_thresh)]=1
    
    combined_ch=np.zeros_like(binary_a)
    combined_ch[(binary_l==1)|(binary_b==1)]=1
    
    mask=np.zeros_like(combined_ch)
    clahe = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=1.0, tileGridSize=(8,8))
    mask = clahe.apply(mask)
    roi=np.array([[0,height-1],[width/2,height/2],[width-1,height-1]],dtype=np.int32)
    cv2.fillPoly(mask,[roi],1)
    masking=cv2.bitwise_and(combined_ch,mask)
    return masking

#Wrapping HLS_THRES fun with warp

def warp_image(image):
    image=undistort(image,cameramatrix,dist)
    image=cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    width=image.shape[1]
    height=image.shape[0]
    src = np.float32([(570,470),(720, 470),(220,720),(1110,720)])
    dst = np.float32([(450,0),(width-450,0),(450,height),(width-450,height)])
    coords_chk = np.array([[240,720],[1110,720],[720, 470],[570,470]], np.int32)
    coords_chk = coords_chk.reshape((-1,1,2))
    img_copy = img.copy()
    cv2.polylines(img_copy,[coords_chk],True,(255,0,0), thickness=4)
    im_size=(img_copy.shape[1],img_copy.shape[0])
    threshold=hls_thres(image)
    M=cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(src,dst)
    M_inv=cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(dst,src)
    warped=cv2.warpPerspective(threshold,M,im_size,flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
    return warped

img=cv2.imread("test_images/test2.jpg")

# Sliding window function to fit polynomial to binary image and histogram for lower half of image
def sliding_window(image):
    hist = np.sum(image[image.shape[0]//2:,:], axis=0)
    half_point = np.int(hist.shape[0]//2)
    #adding quarter point gave better accuracy
    half_half_point = np.int(half_point//2)
    # Find position of left and right lane
    #leftx_pos = np.argmax(hist[:half_point]) 
    #rightx_pos = np.argmax(hist[half_point:]) + half_point
    leftx_pos = np.argmax(hist[half_half_point:half_point]) + half_half_point
    rightx_pos = np.argmax(hist[half_point:(half_point+half_half_point)]) + half_point
    # Identify the x and y positions of all nonzero pixels in the image
    non_zero = image.nonzero()
    non_zeroy = np.array(non_zero[0])
    non_zerox = np.array(non_zero[1])
    # No. of windows and window height 
    num_windows = 12 #10 is giving decent results 12 was working too
    win_height = np.int(image.shape[0]/num_windows)
    # Current positions to be updated for each window
    left_lanex = leftx_pos
    right_lanex = rightx_pos
    delta = 60 # Windows width delta 
    minpix = 40 # Minimum pixels to recenter window
    # Left and right lane pixel indices
    left_lane_pix = []
    right_lane_pix = []
    # Rectangle data display
    rect_disp = []

    for win in range(num_windows):
        min_y = image.shape[0] - (win+1)*win_height
        max_y = image.shape[0] - win*win_height
        min_leftx = left_lanex - delta
        max_leftx = left_lanex + delta
        min_rightx = right_lanex - delta
        max_rightx = right_lanex + delta
        rect_disp.append((min_y, max_y, min_leftx, max_leftx,min_rightx, max_rightx))
        # Identifying nonzero pixels in x and y
        good_left_pix = ((non_zeroy >= min_y) & (non_zeroy < max_y) & (non_zerox >= min_leftx) & (non_zerox < max_leftx)).nonzero()[0]
        good_right_pix = ((non_zeroy >= min_y) & (non_zeroy < max_y) & (non_zerox >=min_rightx) & (non_zerox < max_rightx)).nonzero()[0]
        # Append pixel indices to the lists
        left_lane_pix.append(good_left_pix)
        right_lane_pix.append(good_right_pix)
        #Dynamic window positioning
        if len(good_left_pix) > minpix:
            left_lanex = np.int(np.mean(non_zerox[good_left_pix]))
        if len(good_right_pix) > minpix:        
            right_lanex = np.int(np.mean(non_zerox[good_right_pix]))
            
    left_lane_pix = np.concatenate(left_lane_pix)
    right_lane_pix = np.concatenate(right_lane_pix)

    leftx = non_zerox[left_lane_pix]
    lefty = non_zeroy[left_lane_pix] 
    rightx = non_zerox[right_lane_pix]
    righty = non_zeroy[right_lane_pix] 

    left_fit, right_fit = (None, None)
    # 2nd order polyfit
    if len(leftx) != 0:
        left_fit = np.polyfit(lefty, leftx, 2)
    if len(rightx) != 0:
        right_fit = np.polyfit(righty, rightx, 2)
    
    display_data = (rect_disp, hist)
    
    return left_fit, right_fit, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix, display_data

# Using last fit values
def poly_last_fit(warp1, left_fit_last, right_fit_last):
    delta = 60
    non_zero = warp1.nonzero()
    non_zeroy = np.array(non_zero[0])
    non_zerox = np.array(non_zero[1])
    left_lane_pix = ((non_zerox > (left_fit_last[0]*(non_zeroy**2) + left_fit_last[1]*non_zeroy + left_fit_last[2] - delta)) & 
                      (non_zerox < (left_fit_last[0]*(non_zeroy**2) + left_fit_last[1]*non_zeroy + left_fit_last[2] + delta))) 
    right_lane_pix = ((non_zerox > (right_fit_last[0]*(non_zeroy**2) + right_fit_last[1]*non_zeroy + right_fit_last[2] - delta)) & 
                       (non_zerox < (right_fit_last[0]*(non_zeroy**2) + right_fit_last[1]*non_zeroy + right_fit_last[2] + delta)))  
    
    leftx = non_zerox[left_lane_pix]
    lefty = non_zeroy[left_lane_pix] 
    rightx = non_zerox[right_lane_pix]
    righty = non_zeroy[right_lane_pix]
    
    #Polyfit order 2
    left_fit_new, right_fit_new = (None, None)
    if len(leftx) != 0:
        left_fit_new = np.polyfit(lefty, leftx, 2)
    if len(rightx) != 0:
        right_fit_new = np.polyfit(righty, rightx, 2)
    return left_fit_new, right_fit_new, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix

#Radius of curvature and lane offset function

def ROC(img, l_fit, r_fit, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix):
    # For most US state highways lanes 
    ym_per_pix = 3.048/100 #lane line is 10 ft = 3.048 meters
    xm_per_pix = 3.7/378 # lane width is 12 ft = 3.7 meters
    left_curverad, right_curverad, center_dist = (0, 0, 0)
    # Max y value w.r.t ROC
    j = img.shape[0]
    ploty = np.linspace(0, j-1, j)
    y_eval = np.max(ploty)
  
    #x and y positions of all nonzero pixels in the image
    nonzero = img.nonzero()
    nonzeroy = np.array(nonzero[0])
    nonzerox = np.array(nonzero[1])
    # Again, extract left and right line pixel positions
    leftx = nonzerox[left_lane_pix]
    lefty = nonzeroy[left_lane_pix] 
    rightx = nonzerox[right_lane_pix]
    righty = nonzeroy[right_lane_pix]
    
    if len(leftx) != 0 and len(rightx) != 0:
        left_fit_cr = np.polyfit(lefty*ym_per_pix, leftx*xm_per_pix, 2)
        right_fit_cr = np.polyfit(righty*ym_per_pix, rightx*xm_per_pix, 2)
        # New radious of curvature
        left_curverad = ((1 + (2*left_fit_cr[0]*y_eval*ym_per_pix + left_fit_cr[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*left_fit_cr[0])
        right_curverad = ((1 + (2*right_fit_cr[0]*y_eval*ym_per_pix + right_fit_cr[1])**2)**1.5) / np.absolute(2*right_fit_cr[0])
        # Now our radius of curvature is in meters
    
    # Distance from center  
    if r_fit is not None and l_fit is not None:
        car_position = img.shape[1]/2
        l_fit_x_int = l_fit[0]*j**2 + l_fit[1]*j + l_fit[2]
        r_fit_x_int = r_fit[0]*j**2 + r_fit[1]*j + r_fit[2]
        lane_center_position = (r_fit_x_int + l_fit_x_int) /2
        center_dist =(car_position - lane_center_position) * xm_per_pix #abs
    return left_curverad, right_curverad, center_dist

#Displaying radious of curvature values
l_roc, r_roc, c_offset = ROC(warp_img, left_fit, right_fit, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix)
print('Radius of curvature:', l_roc, 'm,',r_roc, 'm')
print('Lane offset from center:',  c_offset, 'm')

def lane_fill(img, binary_img, l_fit, r_fit, M_inv):
    new_img = np.copy(img)
    new_img=cv2.cvtColor(new_img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    if l_fit is None or r_fit is None:
        return img
    warp_zero = np.zeros_like(binary_img).astype(np.uint8)
    color_warp = np.dstack((warp_zero, warp_zero, warp_zero))
    width=new_img.shape[1]
    height=new_img.shape[0]
    src = np.float32([(570,470),(720, 470),(220,720),(1110,720)])
    dst = np.float32([(450,0),(width-450,0),(450,height),(width-450,height)])
    
    M_inv=cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(dst,src)
    h,w = binary_img.shape
    ploty = np.linspace(0, h-1, num=h)# to cover same y-range as image
    left_fitx = l_fit[0]*ploty**2 + l_fit[1]*ploty + l_fit[2]
    right_fitx = r_fit[0]*ploty**2 + r_fit[1]*ploty + r_fit[2]

    pts_left = np.array([np.transpose(np.vstack([left_fitx, ploty]))])
    pts_right = np.array([np.flipud(np.transpose(np.vstack([right_fitx, ploty])))])
    pts = np.hstack((pts_left, pts_right))

    # Draw the lane onto the warped blank image
    cv2.fillPoly(color_warp, np.int_([pts]), (0,255, 0))
    cv2.polylines(color_warp, np.int32([pts_left]), isClosed=False, color=(255,0,255), thickness=15)
    cv2.polylines(color_warp, np.int32([pts_right]), isClosed=False, color=(0,0,255), thickness=15)

    # Warping back to original image using M_INV
    newwarp = cv2.warpPerspective(color_warp, M_inv, (w, h)) 
    # Combine the result with the original image
    result = cv2.addWeighted(new_img, 1, newwarp, 0.5, 0)
    return result

def lane_data(img, curv_rad, center_dist):
    copy_img = np.copy(img)
    j = copy_img.shape[0]
    fontFace = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX
    text = 'Radius of Curvature'
    text1 = '{:04.3f}'.format(curv_rad) + 'm'
    cv2.putText(copy_img, text, (20,60), fontFace, 1.6, (255,255,255), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)
    cv2.putText(copy_img, text1,(20,110), fontFace, 1.4, (255,255,255), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)
    if center_dist > 0:
        offset = 'Right'
    elif center_dist < 0:
        offset = 'Left'
    text = offset + ' Center Offset '
    text1 = '{:04.4f}'.format(center_dist)+'m'
    cv2.putText(copy_img, text, (790,60), fontFace, 1.6, (255,255,255), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)
    cv2.putText(copy_img, text1, (1030,110), fontFace, 1.4, (255,255,255), 2, cv2.LINE_AA)
    return copy_img

# Define a class to receive the characteristics of each line detection
class Line():
    def __init__(self):
        # was the line detected in the last iteration?
        self.detected = False  
        # x values of the last n fits of the line
        self.recent_xfitted = [] 
        #average x values of the fitted line over the last n iterations
        self.bestx = None     
        #polynomial coefficients averaged over the last n iterations
        self.best_fit = None  
        #polynomial coefficients for the most recent fit
        self.current_fit = []  
        #radius of curvature of the line in some units
        self.radius_of_curvature = None 
        #distance in meters of vehicle center from the line
        self.line_base_pos = None 
        #difference in fit coefficients between last and new fits
        self.diffs = np.array([0,0,0], dtype='float') 
        #number of detected pixels
        self.lane_pix = None
        
    def fit_add(self, fit, inds):
        if fit is not None:
            if self.best_fit is not None:
                self.diffs = abs(fit-self.best_fit)
            if (self.diffs[0] > 0.001 or \
               self.diffs[1] > 1.0 or \
               self.diffs[2] > 100.) and \
               len(self.current_fit) > 0:
                self.detected = False
            else:
                self.detected = True
                self.lane_pix = np.count_nonzero(inds)
                self.current_fit.append(fit)
                if len(self.current_fit) > 5:
                    self.current_fit = self.current_fit[len(self.current_fit)-5:]
                self.best_fit = np.average(self.current_fit, axis=0)
        else:
            self.detected = False
            self.current_fit = self.current_fit[:len(self.current_fit)-1]
            if len(self.current_fit) > 0:
                self.best_fit = np.mean(self.current_fit, axis=0)

def plot_fit(img, fit, plot_color):
    if fit is None:
        return img
    new_img = np.copy(img)
    j = new_img.shape[0]
    ploty = np.linspace(0, j-1, j)
    plotx = fit[0]*ploty**2 + fit[1]*ploty + fit[2]
    pts = np.array([np.transpose(np.vstack([plotx, ploty]))])
    cv2.polylines(new_img, np.int32([pts]), isClosed=False, color=plot_color, thickness=6)
    return new_img

def process_image(img):
    new_img = np.copy(img)
    bin_img = warp_image(new_img)
    # if both left and right lines were detected last frame, use polyfit_using_prev_fit, otherwise use sliding window
    if not l_line.detected or not r_line.detected:
        l_fit, r_fit, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix, display_data = sliding_window(bin_img)
    else:
        l_fit, r_fit, left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix = poly_last_fit(bin_img, l_line.best_fit, r_line.best_fit)
        
    # Fit difference defined to be 450 pixels
    if l_fit is not None and r_fit is not None:

        h = img.shape[0]
        l_fit_x_int = l_fit[0]*h**2 + l_fit[1]*h + l_fit[2]
        r_fit_x_int = r_fit[0]*h**2 + r_fit[1]*h + r_fit[2]
        x_int_diff = abs(r_fit_x_int-l_fit_x_int)
        if abs(450 - x_int_diff) > 100:
            l_fit = None
            r_fit = None
            
    l_line.fit_add(l_fit, left_lane_pix)
    r_line.fit_add(r_fit, right_lane_pix)
    
    # draw the current best fit if it exists
    if l_line.best_fit is not None and r_line.best_fit is not None:
        img_lane_fill = lane_fill(new_img, bin_img, l_line.best_fit, r_line.best_fit, M_inv)
        l_roc, l_roc, c_offset = ROC(bin_img, l_line.best_fit, r_line.best_fit, 
                                                              left_lane_pix, right_lane_pix)
        img_lane = lane_data(img_lane_fill, (l_roc+r_roc)/2, c_offset)
    else:
        img_lane = new_img  
    return img_lane
